In order to solve the ODE (2.27) representing growth in each layer, a boundary condition must be specified on the velocity. However, because (2.27) is first order, one is unable to specify the velocity at both the inner and outer boundaries of each layer. We therefore set the radial velocity to zero on the outer wall, so that all growth occurs inwardly (this choice is discussed further in Sect. 4). Additionally, we require the velocity and displacement at the interface of the two layers to be continuous. Hence, we have 2.31a\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
