We observe similar amounts of remodelling for increases in both tensile and compressive stress-modulated phenotype switching rate and decreasing agonist clearance rate with no clear threshold effect (see Online Resource 6). For the same parameter ranges, agonist resolution times are observed to be similar and relatively independent of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
